msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.73:0.2"
msgid "8. Apaṇṇakavagga"
msgstr "8. Guaranteed"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: asappurisavadhukāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.73:0.3"
msgid "73. Sappurisasutta"
msgstr "73. A Good Person"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.73:1.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato asappuriso veditabbo."
msgstr "“Mendicants, a bad person can be known by four qualities."

msgctxt "an4.73:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.73:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti parassa avaṇṇo taṃ apuṭṭhopi pātu "
"karoti, ko pana vādo puṭṭhassa."
msgstr ""
"To start with, a bad person speaks ill of another even when not asked, how "
"much more so when asked."

msgctxt "an4.73:1.4"
msgid ""
"Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto ahāpetvā alambitvā paripūraṃ vitthārena parassa "
"avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"But when led on by questions they speak ill of another in full detail, not "
"leaving anything out."

msgctxt "an4.73:1.5"
msgid "Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti."
msgstr "That’s how to know that this is a bad person."

#. </p><p>
